Policy
Policy
OneSoft Studio
We at OneSoft Studio take the protection of your personal data very seriously and strictly abide by the regulations of the world data protection act. Personal data will only be collected to an extent that is technically required. In no case this data will be sold or passed on to third parties for any other reasons.
The following declaration gives you an overview on how this protection is guaranteed and which kind of data is collected for which purposes.
AUTOMATICALLY COLLECTED INFORMATION
In addition, the Application may collect certain information automatically, including, but not limited to, the type of mobile device you use, your mobile devices unique device ID, the IP address of your mobile device, your mobile operating system, the type of mobile Internet browsers fine tune our product.
We can also collect data from our partners if you link a third party tool with the Service (such as Facebook or Google).
We do not gather any data from the child other than first name and reading age. This is only stored locally on the device and is optional. It never leaves the device, and will be erased if the user deletes the app.
USE OF DATA:
To provide and maintain our Service
To notify you about changes to our Service
To allow you to participate in interactive features of our Service when you choose to do so
To provide customer support
To gather analysis or valuable information so that we can improve our Service
To monitor the usage of our Service
To detect, prevent and address technical issues
DOES THE APPLICATION COLLECT PRECISE REAL TIME LOCATION INFORMATION OF THE DEVICE?
This Application does not collect precise information about the location of your mobile device. if OneSoft Studio is involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of its assets, you will be notified via email and/or a prominent notice on our Web site of any change in ownership or uses of this information, as well as any choices you.
YOUR RIGHTS AND OPTIONS
Opt-out of marketing emails and other direct marketing.
You may opt-out of receiving promotional communications, such as marketing emails from us by following the instructions in such communications.
Opt-out of targeted advertising.
You can opt-out of interest-based advertising on mobile applications by checking the privacy settings of your Android or iOS device and selecting "limit ad tracking" (Apple iOS) or "opt-out of interest based ads" (Android).
Your other rights.
You also have the right to correct your data, have your data deleted, object how we use or share your data, and restrict how we use or share your data. You can always withdraw your consent, for example by turning off GPS location sharing in your mobile device settings.
We will respond to all requests within a reasonable timeframe. If you have an unresolved privacy or data use concern that we have not addressed satisfactorily, please contact contact@rocketstudio.com.vn.
DATA RETENTION POLICY, MANAGING YOUR INFORMATION
We will retain User Provided data for as long as you use the Application and for a reasonable time thereafter. We will retain Automatically Collected information for up to one year and thereafter may store it in aggregate. If you’d like us to delete User Provided Data that you have provided via the Application, please contact us at OneSoft.studio@gmail.com and we will respond in a reasonable time. Please note that some or all of the User Provided Data may be required in order for the Application to function properly.
SECURITY
We are concerned about safeguarding the confidentiality of your information. We provide physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards to protect information we process and maintain. For example, we limit access to this information to authorized employees and contractors who need to know that information in order to operate, develop or improve our Application.
Please be aware that, although we endeavor provide reasonable security for information we process and maintain, no security system can prevent all potential security breaches.
CHANGES
This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time for any reason. We will notify you of any changes to our Privacy Policy by posting the new Privacy Policy.
AGE LIMITS
We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal data about or direct or target interest based advertising to anyone under the age of 13 or knowingly allow such persons to use our Services. If you are under 13, please do not send any data about yourself to us, including your name, address, telephone number, or email address. No one under the age of 13 may provide any personal data. If we learn that we have collected personal data about a child under age 13, we will delete that data as quickly as possible. If you believe that we might have any data from or about a child under the age of 13, please contact us.
CONTACT US
If you want to contact us about any of the matters in relation to this privacy policy, including to exercise any of your rights, then please contact our customer services department by emailing: contact@rocketstudio.com.vn
US RESIDENTS:
Additional Privacy Information for Virginia Residents:
Following the requirements of VCDPA to protect Virginia users: Our privacy policy aligns with the Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act (VCDPA) by ensuring transparency, data security, and consumer rights protection. We limit personal data collection to what is necessary and relevant for disclosed purposes and do not process data for unrelated purposes without user consent. Our security measures protect the confidentiality and integrity of personal information. We do not discriminate against consumers exercising their rights, including opting out of data sales, targeted advertising, or profiling. Sensitive data is processed only with consent, and we comply with federal laws for children’s data protection. Our policy provides clear details on data categories collected, shared third parties, and secure methods for consumers to exercise their rights, including appeals.
Additional Privacy Information for California Residents:
Following the requirements of CCPA to protect California users: Our privacy policy is designed to comply with the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), including Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.130(a)(5) and 11 C.C.R. § 7011(e)(2). We provide consumers with a clear and accessible privacy notice that details the categories of personal data collected, the purposes for processing, and the rights granted under the CCPA. These rights include the ability to access, correct, and delete personal information, as well as opt out of the sale or sharing of data. We disclose whether personal data is shared with third parties and provide a straightforward process for submitting privacy requests. Our policy ensures that consumers are not discriminated against for exercising their rights. Additionally, we maintain reasonable security measures to protect consumer data and regularly update our privacy practices to remain compliant with California regulations."
We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring transparency in how your personal data is handled. You have the right to know whether your personal information is shared or sold, as well as to whom and for what purposes. Additionally, you have the right to opt out of the sharing or sale of your personal data at any time. To request this information or submit an opt-out request, please contact us at contact@rocketstudio.com.vn with the subject line "Data Inquiry" or "Opt-Out Request." Furthermore, you have the right to request access to the personal data we collect about you. Upon verifying your identity, we will provide details about the categories and specific pieces of personal data we have on file, in accordance with applicable privacy laws.
For information collected under this Privacy Policy, the data controller is Rocket Game Studio. Our Data Protection Officer can be contacted here: contact@rocketstudio.com.vn
